question:
District category contains School District, Medical District, and Research Park.
Supermarkets category contains Stop & Shop, H-E-B, and Aldi.
Product category contains Plant-based Cheese, Salsa, and Yogurt Covered Raisins.
The number of each H-E-B 's Plant-based Cheese equals 4.
The number of each Medical District 's Aldi equals 17 more than each Aldi 's Yogurt Covered Raisins.
The number of each Aldi 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 15.
The number of each School District 's H-E-B equals 21.
The number of each Research Park 's Stop & Shop equals 22 more than each Research Park 's H-E-B.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Plant-based Cheese equals each Medical District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each H-E-B 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 20 times the sum of each Aldi 's Yogurt Covered Raisins, each Medical District 's Aldi, and each School District 's Aldi.
The number of each H-E-B 's Salsa equals each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt Covered Raisins.
The number of each School District 's Aldi equals the sum of each Aldi 's Yogurt Covered Raisins, each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt Covered Raisins, and each Research Park 's H-E-B.
The number of each Aldi 's Plant-based Cheese equals 21.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 10.
The number of each Research Park 's H-E-B equals 8 times each Medical District 's Aldi.
How many Plant-based Cheese does H-E-B have?
solution: Define each H-E-B 's Plant-based Cheese as L; So L = 4.
